{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/network/internetworking-&-ip/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Kooku's log","author":"Kooku","siteUrl":"https://kooku.netlify.com","comment":{"disqusShortName":"","utterances":"koomg9599/kooku-s-log"},"sponsor":{"buyMeACoffeeId":"kooku"}}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0091a33e-9154-572d-b98d-20d1f1e9ecf3","excerpt":"Index Internetworking What & Why ? How ? 다른 계층에서의 Internetworking - Bridge vs Router IP Service Model IP(Internet Protocol) Best Effort Service Model ? 논리 네트워크/주소 vs 물리 네트워크/주소 네트워크 주소는 누가 어떻게 할당하는가? IP Address & ARP 클래스 기반 계층적 주소 구조 ARP는 무엇의 약자인가? ARP가 필요한 이유는? Forwarding vs…","html":"<h3 id=\"index\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#index\" aria-label=\"index permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Index</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Internetworking</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What &#x26; Why ? How ?</li>\n<li>다른 계층에서의 Internetworking - Bridge vs Router</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>IP Service Model</p>\n<ul>\n<li>IP(Internet Protocol) Best Effort Service Model ?</li>\n<li>논리 네트워크/주소 vs 물리 네트워크/주소</li>\n<li>네트워크 주소는 누가 어떻게 할당하는가?</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>IP Address &#x26; ARP</p>\n<ul>\n<li>클래스 기반 계층적 주소 구조</li>\n<li>ARP는 무엇의 약자인가? ARP가 필요한 이유는?</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Forwarding vs Routing</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Forwarding과 Routing의 차이</li>\n<li>Forwarding/Routing Table의 이해</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Fragmentation &#x26; Reassembly</p>\n<ul>\n<li>MTU는 무엇의 약자인가?</li>\n<li>Fragmentation &#x26; Reassembly, 필요한 이유는?</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"1-internetworking\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#1-internetworking\" aria-label=\"1 internetworking permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. Internetworking</h2>\n<h3 id=\"internetwork---what\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#internetwork---what\" aria-label=\"internetwork   what permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>internetwork - What</h3>\n<p>internetwork는 inter + network로 분리할 수 있으며 이를 풀어서 설명하자면 네트워크간의 통신입니다.</p>\n<p>이러한 네트워크간의 통시능로 실제 network는 물리적으로 여러개 이지만 이를 묶어서 논리적으로 하나의 network로 만들어 버립니다.</p>\n<p>Network of Networks  ==> internetwork / internetworking</p>\n<h3 id=\"internetworking---how\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#internetworking---how\" aria-label=\"internetworking   how permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Internetworking - How</h3>\n<p>이 부분은 뒤에서 다시 자세히 설명하도록 하겠습니다.</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 27.027027027027025%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"internetwork01\" title=\"internetwork01\" src=\"/static/b3f0101305351b107ab8551924d89745/fcda8/internetwork01.png\" srcset=\"/static/b3f0101305351b107ab8551924d89745/12f09/internetwork01.png 148w,\n/static/b3f0101305351b107ab8551924d89745/e4a3f/internetwork01.png 295w,\n/static/b3f0101305351b107ab8551924d89745/fcda8/internetwork01.png 590w,\n/static/b3f0101305351b107ab8551924d89745/efc66/internetwork01.png 885w,\n/static/b3f0101305351b107ab8551924d89745/c83ae/internetwork01.png 1180w,\n/static/b3f0101305351b107ab8551924d89745/0e904/internetwork01.png 1384w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Routing - internetworking in Network Layer</p>\n<ul>\n<li>물리망의 다양성, 이질성을 효과적으로 대처하는 구조</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 41.891891891891895%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"internetwork02\" title=\"internetwork02\" src=\"/static/c30a0bc9af882eceec666e5b49d91693/fcda8/internetwork02.png\" srcset=\"/static/c30a0bc9af882eceec666e5b49d91693/12f09/internetwork02.png 148w,\n/static/c30a0bc9af882eceec666e5b49d91693/e4a3f/internetwork02.png 295w,\n/static/c30a0bc9af882eceec666e5b49d91693/fcda8/internetwork02.png 590w,\n/static/c30a0bc9af882eceec666e5b49d91693/efc66/internetwork02.png 885w,\n/static/c30a0bc9af882eceec666e5b49d91693/c83ae/internetwork02.png 1180w,\n/static/c30a0bc9af882eceec666e5b49d91693/46e30/internetwork02.png 1303w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<p>두개의 그림 중 위의 그림을 한번 보겠습니다.</p>\n<p>다국적 사람들이 여러개의 언어로 소통을 하게 되면 서로의 언어를 이해하지 못하여 소통이 어려워지게됩니다. 이걸 이질성이라고 부릅니다.</p>\n<p>이를 해결하기 위하여 Esperanto라는 언어를 새로 만들고 이것으로 소통을 하게된다면 어떨까요? 자신의 언어를 Esperanto로 변환한 후 다른 국적의 사람에게 전달한다면 그사람은 이해할 수 있을 겁니다.</p>\n<p>network service에서의 Esperanto를 IP 즉 ‘Internet Protocol’이라고 부릅니다.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Bridging - internetworking in Data Link Layer</p>\n<ul>\n<li>IEEE 002 LAN라는 공통 기술을 사용하는 망들을 결합해 논리적으로 하나인 연동망을 형성하는 것</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Repeater - Digital 통신에서 복원하는 역할이며 Analog에서는 Amplify(증폭)를 사용합니다.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"2-important-problems\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2-important-problems\" aria-label=\"2 important problems permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2 important Problems</h4>\n<p>internetworking에서는 두가지 문제점들이 있으며 이는 매우 중요한 문제이기에 외우는 걸 장려합니다.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Heterogeneity</strong>: 이질성</li>\n<li><strong>Scalability</strong>: 규모확장성</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"ip-internet\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ip-internet\" aria-label=\"ip internet permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>IP Internet</h3>\n<p>위에서 Network간의 이질성 문제를 해결하기 위해서 IP라는 것을 사용한다는 사실을 알 수 있었습니다. 이 IP를 어떻게 사용할까요?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Concatenation of Networks</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 344px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 77.02702702702703%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"ip02\" title=\"ip02\" src=\"/static/fb91dd5d3690d595a14f2e6491804dd4/75d93/ip02.png\" srcset=\"/static/fb91dd5d3690d595a14f2e6491804dd4/12f09/ip02.png 148w,\n/static/fb91dd5d3690d595a14f2e6491804dd4/e4a3f/ip02.png 295w,\n/static/fb91dd5d3690d595a14f2e6491804dd4/75d93/ip02.png 344w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 344px) 100vw, 344px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Protocol Stacks</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 25.675675675675674%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"ip01\" title=\"ip01\" src=\"/static/ea0f71a3d35e1582c20080d6f6c8631e/fcda8/ip01.png\" srcset=\"/static/ea0f71a3d35e1582c20080d6f6c8631e/12f09/ip01.png 148w,\n/static/ea0f71a3d35e1582c20080d6f6c8631e/e4a3f/ip01.png 295w,\n/static/ea0f71a3d35e1582c20080d6f6c8631e/fcda8/ip01.png 590w,\n/static/ea0f71a3d35e1582c20080d6f6c8631e/efc66/ip01.png 885w,\n/static/ea0f71a3d35e1582c20080d6f6c8631e/c83ae/ip01.png 1180w,\n/static/ea0f71a3d35e1582c20080d6f6c8631e/252a4/ip01.png 1314w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>위에 보시는 두가지 특성이 IP를 이용해서 통신하는 방법입니다.</p>\n<p>Application(Network)는 자신의 Data를 IP Datagram(Common Box)에 넣어서 다른 Application(Network)에게 보내게 됩니다.</p>\n<p>양끝단의 Application(Network)는 중간단계를 생각하지 않고 전송된 IP Datagram만 풀어서 읽으면 됩니다. 이를 <strong>End To End Principle</strong> 이라고 부릅니다.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>만약 Data의 손실이 있을때에는 TCP가 재전송 요청을 합니다. IP는 Data 손실을 해결해주지 않습니다.(unreliable)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>그리고 이때 IP 이동 Layer(2번째 그림의 빨간 박스)를 <strong>Common Logical Layer</strong>라고 부릅니다.</p>\n<h2 id=\"2-ip-service-model\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2-ip-service-model\" aria-label=\"2 ip service model permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. IP Service Model</h2>\n<p>IP의 특징은 밑의 두가지 특징이 있습니다.</p>\n<h4 id=\"1-simple\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#1-simple\" aria-label=\"1 simple permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. Simple</h4>\n<p>IP는 매우 간편합니다. 전송하고자 하는 Data를 Datagram에 넣어서 보내면 되죠.</p>\n<p>그래서 IP Service를 <strong>Datagram-based connectionless service</strong> 또는 <strong>Connectionless Service</strong>라고 부릅니다.</p>\n<h4 id=\"2-unreliable-no-garantee\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2-unreliable-no-garantee\" aria-label=\"2 unreliable no garantee permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. unreliable (No Garantee)</h4>\n<p>IP는 Data 무결성과 순서를 보장해주지 않습니다. 그래서 IP Service는 <strong>Best-effort delivery</strong>만 수행할 뿐 unreliable하다고 말합니다.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>packets may be lost, deliverer out of order, duplicated</li>\n<li>packets can be delayed for a long time</li>\n</ul>\n<p>=> IP doesn’t care these problems</p>\n<p>이러한 문제는 End(TCP)가 해결합니다. (End to End Principle)</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 431px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 62.83783783783784%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"ip03\" title=\"ip03\" src=\"/static/464df3b36aea69375836c37355e97229/9cb4e/ip03.png\" srcset=\"/static/464df3b36aea69375836c37355e97229/12f09/ip03.png 148w,\n/static/464df3b36aea69375836c37355e97229/e4a3f/ip03.png 295w,\n/static/464df3b36aea69375836c37355e97229/9cb4e/ip03.png 431w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 431px) 100vw, 431px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<p>위의 그림은 IP Datagram이며 여기서 SourceAddr과 DestinationAddr에 IP 주소가 들어갑니다.</p>\n<h3 id=\"logical-networkaddress-vs-physical-networkaddress\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#logical-networkaddress-vs-physical-networkaddress\" aria-label=\"logical networkaddress vs physical networkaddress permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Logical Network/Address vs Physical Network/Address</h3>\n<p><strong>Physical Address</strong>: 48bit의 MAC 주소입니다.</p>\n<p><strong>Logical Address</strong>: 32bit이며 Network + Host ID로 이루어져 있습니다.</p>\n<h2 id=\"3-ip-address--arp\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#3-ip-address--arp\" aria-label=\"3 ip address  arp permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>3. IP Address &#x26; ARP</h2>\n<h3 id=\"ip-address-ipv4\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ip-address-ipv4\" aria-label=\"ip address ipv4 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>IP Address (IPv4)</h3>\n<p>IP주소는 <strong>클래스 기반 계층 구조</strong>입니다.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>계층 주소 구조 : Network + Host</strong> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>동일 Network의 Host는 동일한 Network ID/Address를 가짐</li>\n<li>Scalability를 고려한 디자인 : Routing Table을 개별 Host 단위가 아닌 Network 단위로 구성할 수 있음</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>클래스 기반 주소 :</strong> <strong>계층 구조 필드 길이가 클래스에 따라 다름</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Class A, B, C – 네트워크 크기를 고려하여 배정</li>\n<li>Class D : 1110 + Multicast Address ; Class E : 1111~ : Reserved</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 43.91891891891892%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"ip04\" title=\"ip04\" src=\"/static/38b190e6ee107bf0662e63b702e6202d/fcda8/ip04.png\" srcset=\"/static/38b190e6ee107bf0662e63b702e6202d/12f09/ip04.png 148w,\n/static/38b190e6ee107bf0662e63b702e6202d/e4a3f/ip04.png 295w,\n/static/38b190e6ee107bf0662e63b702e6202d/fcda8/ip04.png 590w,\n/static/38b190e6ee107bf0662e63b702e6202d/efc66/ip04.png 885w,\n/static/38b190e6ee107bf0662e63b702e6202d/6937a/ip04.png 1094w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<h3 id=\"subnetting--subnet-mask\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#subnetting--subnet-mask\" aria-label=\"subnetting  subnet mask permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Subnetting &#x26; subnet mask</h3>\n<p>subnetting은 scalable을 위해 등장하였습니다. </p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 39.86486486486486%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"ip05\" title=\"ip05\" src=\"/static/0d3f96dd431365b205847eb2a1d3fb5d/fcda8/ip05.png\" srcset=\"/static/0d3f96dd431365b205847eb2a1d3fb5d/12f09/ip05.png 148w,\n/static/0d3f96dd431365b205847eb2a1d3fb5d/e4a3f/ip05.png 295w,\n/static/0d3f96dd431365b205847eb2a1d3fb5d/fcda8/ip05.png 590w,\n/static/0d3f96dd431365b205847eb2a1d3fb5d/efc66/ip05.png 885w,\n/static/0d3f96dd431365b205847eb2a1d3fb5d/c83ae/ip05.png 1180w,\n/static/0d3f96dd431365b205847eb2a1d3fb5d/c1b63/ip05.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<p>subnetting을 통해서 같은 Network ID에서도 Host ID를 다시 나누어 SubNetwork를 만들 수가 있게 됩니다.</p>\n<p>이렇게 만들어진 SubNet 단위별로 Routing Table에 저장하여 Entry로 사용하게 되는겁니다.</p>\n<p>이번에는 subnet ID의 크기를 구해봅시다.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">164.125.38.0/24</code> 다음과 같은 ip주소가 있다고 해봅시다. </p>\n<p>우선 위의 IP는 B 클래스로 Network ID는 16bit, Host ID는 16bit라는 것을 알 수 있습니다. 이때 ’/’ 뒤에 있는 숫자는 subnet mask의 길이로 우리는 subnet mask가 24bit라는 것을 알 수 있습니다. 따라서 subnet ID의 길이는 24 - 16 = 8bit가 되겠네요.</p>\n<h3 id=\"개별-hostdevice에-할당할-수-없는-ip-주소\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#%EA%B0%9C%EB%B3%84-hostdevice%EC%97%90-%ED%95%A0%EB%8B%B9%ED%95%A0-%EC%88%98-%EC%97%86%EB%8A%94-ip-%EC%A3%BC%EC%86%8C\" aria-label=\"개별 hostdevice에 할당할 수 없는 ip 주소 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>개별 Host/Device에 할당할 수 없는 IP 주소</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Network Address</strong> <strong>: 네트워크 그 자체를 식별하기 위해 사용</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Host 주소 필드의 모든 bit 값이 0 Ex) <strong>164.125.0.0</strong> </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Broadcast Address</strong> <strong>: 네트워크 내의 모든 호스트에게 패킷을 방송하기 위해 사용</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>255.255.255.255</strong> : Local Broadcast; Routers do not traditionally pass broadcast address.</li>\n<li>All Host Broadcast : Host 주소 필드의 모든 bit 값이 1 – <strong>Directed Broadcast</strong> </li>\n</ul>\n<p>–Ex) <strong>164.125.255.255</strong> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cf) Multicast Address – Class D Address, Cf) Unicast, Broadcast, Multicast, Anycast</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Loopback Address</strong> <strong>:</strong> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>127.<em>.</em>.* : 자기 스스로를 목적지로 하는 IP 주소, 주로 <strong>127.0.0.1</strong></li>\n<li>0.0.0.0 : IP가 할당되지 않은 상황에서 bootstrap 시 소스 주소로 사용</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Private Addresses</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Can be used only on a private network ! 🡪 NAT/PAT에서 설명</li>\n<li>Class A : <strong>10.0.0.0</strong> – 10.255.255.255 / 8 prefix</li>\n<li>Class B : 172.16.0.0 – 172.31.255.255 / 12 prefix</li>\n<li>Class C : <strong>192.168.0.0</strong> – 192.168.255.255 / 16 prefix</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"arp-address-resolution-protocol\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#arp-address-resolution-protocol\" aria-label=\"arp address resolution protocol permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>ARP (Address Resolution Protocol)</h3>\n<p>Data Link Layer에서의 MAC주소(Ethernet)를 얻기 위해 ARP를 사용합니다.</p>\n<h4 id=\"address-translation-with-arp\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#address-translation-with-arp\" aria-label=\"address translation with arp permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Address Translation with ARP</h4>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 61.48648648648649%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"arp01\" title=\"arp01\" src=\"/static/c579e442a9ab67306fc32744587a1ec3/1c72d/arp01.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/c579e442a9ab67306fc32744587a1ec3/a80bd/arp01.jpg 148w,\n/static/c579e442a9ab67306fc32744587a1ec3/1c91a/arp01.jpg 295w,\n/static/c579e442a9ab67306fc32744587a1ec3/1c72d/arp01.jpg 590w,\n/static/c579e442a9ab67306fc32744587a1ec3/30e56/arp01.jpg 679w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<p>ARP는 broadcast로 해당 IP주소에 대한 Ethernet 주소를 요청합니다. 그래서 모든 network이 이 요청을 들으며, 해당 IP주소를 B는 응답으로 MAC address를 전송합니다. 이때 reply또한 broadcast로 전송되며 다른 network들도 중복된 요청을 하지 않도록 <strong>ARP Cashe</strong>에 해당 ip와 MAC address를 저장합니다.</p>\n<h2 id=\"4-forwarding-vs-routing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#4-forwarding-vs-routing\" aria-label=\"4 forwarding vs routing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>4. Forwarding vs Routing</h2>\n<p>Forwarding 과 Routing을 구분하는 것은 조금 애매한 부분입니다. 하지만 여기에서는 다음과 같이 정의하겠습니다.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Forwarding</strong>: Forwarding/Routing Table을 이용하여 입력 받은 패킷을 적절한 출력으로 내보내는 작업 (어디로 보낼지 선택하는 작업)</li>\n<li><strong>Routing</strong>: Forwarding/Routing Table을 만드는 작업</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"ip-forwarding-algorithm\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ip-forwarding-algorithm\" aria-label=\"ip forwarding algorithm permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>IP Forwarding Algorithm</h4>\n<p>match 된 것들 중에 Netmask가 제일 긴 것에 보내라.</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 23.64864864864865%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"forwarding01\" title=\"forwarding01\" src=\"/static/14982fefbc32f106b3d2c7fb6c025f21/fcda8/forwarding01.png\" srcset=\"/static/14982fefbc32f106b3d2c7fb6c025f21/12f09/forwarding01.png 148w,\n/static/14982fefbc32f106b3d2c7fb6c025f21/e4a3f/forwarding01.png 295w,\n/static/14982fefbc32f106b3d2c7fb6c025f21/fcda8/forwarding01.png 590w,\n/static/14982fefbc32f106b3d2c7fb6c025f21/efc66/forwarding01.png 885w,\n/static/14982fefbc32f106b3d2c7fb6c025f21/b5cea/forwarding01.png 1140w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<h3 id=\"nat-network-address-translation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#nat-network-address-translation\" aria-label=\"nat network address translation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>NAT: Network Address Translation</h3>\n<p>  IP 패킷의 TCP/UDP 포트 숫자와 소스 및 목적지의 IP 주소 등을 재기록하면서 라우터를 통해 네트워크 트래픽을 주고 받는 기술을 말합니다.</p>\n<p>  NAT는 IPv4의 주소 부족 문제를 해결하기 위한 방법으로서 고려되었으며, 주로 비공인(사설, local) 네트워크 주소를 사용하는 망에서 외부의 공인망(public, 예를 들면 인터넷)과의 통신을 위해서 네트워크 주소를 변환하는 것입니다. </p>\n<h4 id=\"nat-types\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#nat-types\" aria-label=\"nat types permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>NAT Types</h4>\n<p><strong>1) Static NAT</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed 1:1 mappings between private addresses and public address</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2) Dynamic NAT</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>When a public address is needed, choose a public address dynamically from the address pool and assign it</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>3) PAT (Port Address Translation)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>가장 많이 사용하는 방법</li>\n<li>Only one public IP address is used</li>\n<li>Port Number로 구별한다.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"5-fragmentation--reassembly\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#5-fragmentation--reassembly\" aria-label=\"5 fragmentation  reassembly permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>5. Fragmentation &#x26; Reassembly</h2>\n<p>Each (physical) Network has some MTU</p>\n<ul>\n<li>MTU : Maximum Transmission Unit (IP Datagram이 MTU보다 크면 사용)</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 120.94594594594594%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"mtu01\" title=\"mtu01\" src=\"/static/bc00e2af36dd87d367483159595d961d/1c72d/mtu01.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/bc00e2af36dd87d367483159595d961d/a80bd/mtu01.jpg 148w,\n/static/bc00e2af36dd87d367483159595d961d/1c91a/mtu01.jpg 295w,\n/static/bc00e2af36dd87d367483159595d961d/1c72d/mtu01.jpg 590w,\n/static/bc00e2af36dd87d367483159595d961d/fdf7c/mtu01.jpg 598w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<p>보내려는 Data의 양이 MTU보다 크므로 쪼개서 보내게 됩니다. 이때 offset은 fragment된 패킷들의 순서를 나타내고 flag는 마지막인지 뒤에 더 있는지를 표시합니다. 마지막으로 ID는 같은 것의 조각이라는 것을 표시합니다.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"internetworking & IP","date":"September 23, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/network/internetworking-&-ip/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/web/http-고속화와-안전성을-추구한-확장/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"HTTP 고속화와 안전성을 추구한 확장","category":"web"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/network/ip-routing-&-protocols/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"IP Routing & Protocols","category":"network"}}}}}